| VIDEO UPDATE |  NEW PRESS CONFERENCE!
-  Search for missing San Antonio child gets $20,000 reward, FBI reviewing footage
- Lina went missing Monday, December 20, from the playground at her family's apartment complex on the 9400 block of Fredericksburg Road. SAPD Chief William McManus said the first hours are very important in a missing person case like this, but added time is passing quickly.
"Early on is very important. Unfortunately, I have to say the longer time lapses the less hopeful we become," McManus said during the press conference. 
- Thank you to everyone who has been coming in, watching, leaving comments. I'm really enjoying all of you and your insights!
